info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 6:46PM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Marion and west central Putnam Counties through 715 PM EDT... At 645 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near Orange Springs, or near Interlachen, moving east at 5 mph. HAZARD...Winds around 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Interlachen, Orange Springs, Hollister, Hog Valley, Johnson and Mannville. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
